00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:47,390
and turn into this relationship, where

98
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:52,060
the probability of the demand being less or equal to Q,

99
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:53,900
my order quantity, is going to be

100
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:58,220
equal to this relationship of c_s the shortage cost,

101
00:04:58,220 --> 00:05:01,470
over the sum of the excess cost and the shortage cost.

102
00:05:01,470 --> 00:05:03,630
Hopefully, this looks really familiar to you.

103
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:06,640
It's the same critical ratio we saw in the EOQ problem

104
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,390
